<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 28 日，星期日 01:18:20 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Increase in Fake Science Publications Threatens Academic Publishing Integrity]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110644156" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0a/1101670225_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_4ea3a5bb8a6a6cba6223c0866c607f95.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1101670208" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/increase-in-fake-science-publications-threatens-academic-publishing-integrity-1110644156.html?share-img=1101670208"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Sang Tan</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">伦敦威斯敏斯特大学的一名研究小组成员通过显微镜观察用于产生抗疟疾抗体的细菌。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="A research team  member looks through a microscope of bacteria use for producing anti-body against malaria at Westminster University in London. - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="伦敦威斯敏斯特大学的一名研究小组成员通过显微镜观察用于产生抗疟疾抗体的细菌。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0a/1101670225_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_9d0f391639cddde86add504ed0465235.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0a/1101670225_0:160:3073:1888_640x0_80_0_0_6085ac0ec3de6503c2938c6daa792ba7.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0a/1101670225_0:160:3073:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_f3abe8dab3de75a5cc74644c6f92d297.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0a/0a/1101670225_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_9d0f391639cddde86add504ed0465235.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Sang Tan </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">学术出版的诚信正面临假科学出版物泛滥的挑战，商业“编辑服务”或“造纸厂”正以惊人的速度生产假科学出版物。后者使用人工智能支持的自动化技术为面临职业发展压力的个人制作虚假出版物。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在他们的研究中，研究人员向科学出版物的作者发送了调查问卷，以确定可能标记假出版物的指标。根据收到的回复，确定了三个指标：作者私人电子邮件的使用、国际合着和医院隶属关系。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些指标随后被用于分析 PubMed® 中列出的 15,120 篇出版物的样本，同时考虑了出版日期、期刊、影响因子和作者所在国家/地区等因素。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该方法使用 400 份已知假出版物和 400 份匹配的推定非假出版物样本进行了验证。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">结果表明，利用两个或三个指标的分类规则的灵敏度分别为86%和90%，误报率分别为44%和37%。该研究还发现，虚假出版物的比例从 2010 年的 16% 增加到 2020 年的 28%。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">将这些发现外推到 2020 年 Scimago 中列出的大约 130 万份生物医学出版物，研究人员估计每年有超过 300,000 份假出版物产生。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>马格德堡奥托冯格里克大学的共同作者 Bernhard Sabel 说：“这太难以置信了”，并将其与“有人告诉你 30% 的食物有毒”的情况进行比较。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110644156" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/increase-in-fake-science-publications-threatens-academic-publishing-integrity-1110644156.html?share-block=1110644162" data-title="&amp;quot;It is just too hard to believe&amp;quot;, says co-author Bernhard Sabel from Otto von Guericke University Magdeburg, comparing it to the situation when &amp;quot;somebody tells you 30% of what you eat is toxic.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员得出结论，他们的简单分类规则可以有效地标记出潜在的假冒出版物，以便进行进一步的审查。他们还强调了虚假出版物的增加率，表明其流行率高于之前报道的水平。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">生物医学领域虚假出版物的泛滥带来了重大风险，包括对科学信任的侵蚀、对公众健康的潜在危害以及对经济支出和安全的影响。检测和撤回虚假出版物对于维护科学记录的完整性至关重要。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">对假出版物的需求源于学生、科学家和医生在学术和政府机构以及大学附属医院的推动下在高影响因子期刊上发表文章所面临的压力。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">优先考虑出版物数量和影响因素作为衡量科学卓越程度的学术政策加剧了这种压力。造纸厂通过提供服务来帮助个人满足出版要求并提升他们的职业生涯，从而利用这一需求。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该研究的作者强调了一起涉及一家造纸厂的未遂腐败事件，该事件联系了其中一家，提出在他们的虚假文章中引用该期刊编辑的内容，以提高该期刊的影响因子。这一事件促使研究人员对全球范围内的虚假出版进行定量分析。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员的方法提供了一种有价值的工具，可以识别生物医学领域潜在的假冒出版物。他们还强调了提高科学界对虚假出版物的存在和影响的认识的重要性。撤回已识别的虚假出版物、实施更严格的同行评审流程以及继续努力提高科学诚信对于应对这一日益严重的威胁至关重要。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “假科学出版可能是有史以来最大的科学骗局，浪费财政资源，减缓医学进步，并可能危及生命，”研究人员写道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110644156" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/increase-in-fake-science-publications-threatens-academic-publishing-integrity-1110644156.html?share-block=1110644169" data-title="&quot;Fake science publishing is possibly the biggest science scam of all times, wasting financial resources, slowing down medical progress, and possibly endangering lives,&quot; write researchers."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">可以通过<a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2023.05.06.23289563" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">MedRxiv</a>服务访问该研究的预印本。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 23:26:50 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/increase-in-fake-science-publications-threatens-academic-publishing-integrity-1110644156.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/increase-in-fake-science-publications-threatens-academic-publishing-integrity-1110644156.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>科学研究</category><category>科学研究</category><category>假货</category><category>学术界</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Air Raid Sirens Go Off in Several Regions of Ukraine, Including Kiev - Authorities]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110644030" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/1c/1108863592_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_e51af9107036c62f92e97e69e4fd945f.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1108863574" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/air-raid-sirens-go-off-in-several-regions-of-ukraine-including-kiev---authorities-1110644030.html?share-img=1108863574"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Stringer</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">一张全景图显示了乌克兰基辅的基辅佩乔尔斯克修道院修道院。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="A general view shows the Kiev Pechersk Lavra monastery in Kiev, Ukraine. - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="一般视图显示了乌克兰基辅的基辅佩乔尔斯克修道院修道院。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/1c/1108863592_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_a7376099ddc325bde115412083f0e5ba.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/1c/1108863592_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_850ec1fe610b2b08e1763959a8e4bd14.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/1c/1108863592_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_2a110710cb1b0b0c7e3f8371f20bf945.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/1c/1108863592_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_a7376099ddc325bde115412083f0e5ba.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 斯特林格</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：根据该国数字化转型部的空袭数据，周六深夜，包括基辅在内的乌克兰多个地区发布了空袭警告。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该部的在线地图显示，午夜过后不久，空袭警报在尼古拉耶夫、基洛沃格勒、切尔尼戈夫、第聂伯罗彼得罗夫斯克和基辅的乌克兰地区以及乌克兰控制的赫尔松地区部分地区响起。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自 10 月 10 日（克里米亚大桥恐怖袭击发生两天后）以来，俄罗斯对乌克兰基础设施实施了精确打击。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">深夜，乌克兰首都基辅以及日托米尔和苏梅地区发布了空袭警报。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2月，乌克兰电网运营商Ukrenergo负责人表示，俄罗斯空袭对乌克兰能源基础设施造成的直接破坏可能高达数亿美元，经济损失达数十亿。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 22:27:06 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/air-raid-sirens-go-off-in-several-regions-of-ukraine-including-kiev---authorities-1110644030.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/air-raid-sirens-go-off-in-several-regions-of-ukraine-including-kiev---authorities-1110644030.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>基辅</category><category>尼古拉耶夫</category><category>乌克兰能源公司</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Putin Says Border Guards to Continue Protecting Russia’s Sovereignty Territorial Integrity]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110643895" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110613082_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_6829d2e48fc4c6f3cba132e55015736c.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110613064" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/putin-says-border-guards-to-continue-protecting-russias-sovereignty-territorial-integrity-1110643895.html?share-img=1110613064"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Mikhail Klimentyev</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Russian President Vladimir Putin - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="俄罗斯总统普京" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110613082_0:0:3071:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_c3f4ed5d43910254907e11a5b3160a7e.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110613082_0:0:3071:1728_640x0_80_0_0_29b3db599a563b4f03f323a0148b097b.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110613082_0:0:3071:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_ca27891e4a28737a0510d73ab62452dd.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1a/1110613082_0:0:3071:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_c3f4ed5d43910254907e11a5b3160a7e.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Mikhail Klimentyev</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京在边防军日向退伍军人和现役军人表示祝贺，称俄罗斯边防军将继续保护国家的主权和领土完整，并将确保军用和民用货物运往新的组成实体俄罗斯。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>“你们，战胜纳粹的胜利者一代的接班人和继承人，继续光荣地、有尊严地履行你们的职责，解决具有挑战性的优先任务，保卫国家边界，开展边境控制和海洋资源保护，为实施国际一体化项目和发展跨境合作、打击跨国犯罪和走私、防止转移和恐怖袭击做出重要贡献，”普京</strong>在周日的声明中说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯总统感谢边防人员的服务，特别是那些参加乌克兰特别军事行动的人员。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">普京说：“我相信，你将继续大公无私、勇敢高效地行动，称职有效地利用一切可用的资源和手段，捍卫俄罗斯的主权和领土完整以及我国人民的安全。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110643895" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/putin-says-border-guards-to-continue-protecting-russias-sovereignty-territorial-integrity-1110643895.html?share-block=1110643898" data-title="&quot;I am confident that you will continue to act selflessly, bravely and efficiently, and will competently and effectively use all available resources and means to protect the sovereignty and territorial integrity of Russia and the security of our people,&quot; Putin said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">总统说，俄罗斯边防部队必须与联邦安全局、武装部队和俄罗斯联邦国民警卫队的其他单位以及地方政府机构密切合作。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “......至关重要的是确保军用和民用车辆和货物，包括食品、人道主义援助和建筑材料在前往俄罗斯联邦新组成实体——顿涅茨克和卢甘斯克人民共和国的途中快速移动，以及扎波罗热和赫尔松地区，”普京说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110643895" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/putin-says-border-guards-to-continue-protecting-russias-sovereignty-territorial-integrity-1110643895.html?share-block=1110643901" data-title="&quot;... it is vitally important to ensure fast movement of both military and civil vehicles and cargoes, including food, humanitarian aid, and construction materials on their way to new constituent entities of the Russian Federation – the Donetsk and Lugansk people’s republics, and the Zaporozhye and Kherson regions,&quot; Putin said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">每年 5 月 28 日在俄罗斯庆祝边防卫队日。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 21:37:33 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/putin-says-border-guards-to-continue-protecting-russias-sovereignty-territorial-integrity-1110643895.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/putin-says-border-guards-to-continue-protecting-russias-sovereignty-territorial-integrity-1110643895.html<category>俄罗斯</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>俄罗斯边防局</category><category>边界</category><category>边境管制</category></item></channel></rss>